This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with pedestrian orientation estimation from camera captures. It may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as the proposed model can be used in autonomous driving. The use of deep learning techniques in the proposed model suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves logical relationships and interpretability of the network structure, which may suggest it belongs to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper may also belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category as it deals with safety measures such as collision avoidance and prewarning.
